Spring Boot Questions
What is Spring Boot, and how is it different from the Spring Framework?
Spring Boot simplifies Spring development by:
Providing auto-configuration to reduce boilerplate code.
Embedding application servers like Tomcat, Jetty, or Undertow for easier deployment.
Integrated dependency management with Starters.
Unlike traditional Spring, it doesnâ€™t require verbose XML or manual configurations.
Explain the use of application.properties or application.yml in Spring Boot.
These files are used for configuring application-level properties, such as:
Server port: server.port=8081
Database configuration: spring.datasource.url, spring.datasource.username, etc.
Logging levels: logging.level.<logger-name>=DEBUG
What are Spring Boot Auto Configuration and @EnableAutoConfiguration?
Auto-Configuration: Automatically configures Spring beans based on classpath dependencies. For example:
spring-boot-starter-data-jpa configures EntityManager and DataSource.
@EnableAutoConfiguration: Enables auto-configuration. It is implicitly included with @SpringBootApplication.
What is a Spring Boot Starter?
Starters are pre-defined dependency descriptors that simplify including libraries. Examples:
spring-boot-starter-web: For REST ful web services.
spring-boot-starter-data-jpa: For JPA and Hibernate.
How does Spring Boot integrate with external configuration sources?
Spring Boot supports hierarchical configuration from multiple sources:
Application properties/yaml files, command-line arguments, environment variables, etc.
External configurations can be loaded from remote sources using tools like Spring Cloud Config or Consul.
Explain Spring Boot Actuator and its role.
Actuator is a tool to monitor and manage Spring Boot applications.
Provides REST endpoints (e.g., /actuator/health, /actuator/metrics) for operational insights on performance, uptime, and resource usage.
What is the difference between DevTools in Spring Boot and Actuator?
DevTools: Facilitates hot-reloading of code in the development environment.
Actuator: Exposes operational endpoints for production usage.
Explain the SpringApplication.run() method in Spring Boot.
It is the entry point of the Spring Boot application.
It bootstraps the application context, starts the embedded web server (if any), and initializes all beans with dependency injection.
